If you're a fan of turn based hexagones tactical battles this is a must have.
I came in hoping a game like Heroes of Might and Magic, but I really got surprised with the tools, storyline and options you're able to explore.
This game will bring you to a medieval world full of disputes for power and glory; different races trying to survive and expand their lands, wealth and people.
Besides that, you're not a mere mortal king or lord, but you're above them all, trying to reach a higher purpose - which you will be able to chose through your fate and will.
Conquering world pieces to build your own or eliminating all lives around, you can do whatever you want in your path.

So I basically recommend this game because:
- Really awesome tactical turn based battles with unique features and options, which you need to explore all resources and be a strategist (depending on game difficulty);
- Interesting concepts evolving into a storyline which you can mold a world depeding on your alingment and convenience, which makes a nice roleplaying;
- Interesting 3D character models (action) and pictures (events) mix;
- Very explicative tutorial that accompanies you throughout the game, appearing when given situation occurs;
- Freedom.

Things I consider negative, but I hope they'll fix in future patches, mostly bugs:
- Crashes when specific situations occur (casting a particular spell or something like that);
- Game forum with restrictions and difficulties in accessing.
